Cellular protein interactions with ncp BVDV2a 1373 Npro were identified in p3XFLAG-Npro transfected 293T cells using co-immunoprecipitation technique. The proteins in cell lysate of p3XFLAG-Npro or p3XFLAG transfected 293T was pulled down (isolated) using anti-FLAG antibody and examined through mass spectrometry. A total 30 most abundant proteins were identified in p3XFLAG as well as in p3XFLAG-Npro transfected cells lysate which mainly included keratin protein for cytoskeletal, ATP synthase, chain B of Immunoglobulin and protein S100A9. In comparing these two groups, a total of sixteen proteins were identified which were present in p3XFLAG-Npro transfected cells that were absent in p3XFLAG transfected cells (Table 1
). Among these proteins, S100A9 had the highest mass spectrometry score (i.e., 295) indicating a strong association between BVDV Npro and cellular S100A9 (Table 1). The further analysis of S100A9 protein using MassLynx software 4.1 (Micromass) revealed 7 peptide fragments (Table 2
).
